The President issued a statement expressing his gratitude for the Senate Foreign Relations Committee's vote in favor of the New START Treaty. He commended the committee members for their thoughtful review of the treaty and highlighted that leaders from both Republican and Democratic administrations have endorsed it. The President emphasized that the treaty reduces the nuclear forces of both the United States and Russia, provides strong verification measures, and strengthens relations between the two nations. He urged the full Senate to quickly approve the treaty and encouraged bipartisan support for its ratification, noting that it would advance American leadership and strengthen national security.